# CLI Usage: Command Line Interface

The [main.py](mdc:absrefined/main.py) file provides a command-line interface for the application with these key options:

- `--server`: AudioBookShelf server URL
- `--book-url`: URL of the book to process (can extract server and item ID automatically)
- `--llm-api`: OpenAI-compatible API URL
- `--model`: LLM model to use
- `--window`: Window size in seconds around each chapter marker
- `--temp-dir`: Directory for temporary files
- `--dry-run`: Don't actually update the server
- `--just-download`: Only download the audio file without processing
- `--verbose`: Enable verbose output

The application also uses environment variables (via .env file) for credentials and API keys.
